Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Schwarzschild Radius
Formula: r_s = 2GM/c²
Note:    Event horizon radius of a black hole

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   DNA Structure
Formula: Double helix; A-T and G-C base pairs
Note:    Stores and transmits genetic information

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Pythagorean Theorem
Formula: a² + b² = c²
Note:    Right triangle relationship; foundation of geometry

Domain:  Geology
Topic:   Age of Earth
Formula: 4.54 billion years
Note:    Determined by radiometric dating of oldest rocks/meteorites

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Boyle's Law
Formula: P₁V₁ = P₂V₂
Note:    Pressure and volume inversely proportional at constant T

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     LSTM
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Gating mechanisms solve vanishing gradient in sequences
Year:        1997
Researchers: Hochreiter/Schmidhuber
Applications:NLP, speech, time series
Related:     GRU, RNN, gates, cell state

Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Gradient Descent
Category:    Optimization
Definition:  Iteratively adjusts parameters to minimize loss function
Year:        1847
Researchers: Cauchy; ML by many
Applications:Training all ML models
Related:     SGD, Adam, momentum, learning rate

